'''Kim Seung-youn''' ({{ko-hhrm|김승연|金昇淵}}; born February 7, 1952) is a South Korean businessman. He is currently the CEO of [[Hanwha]] Group<ref>{{cite news|title=Hanwha boss indicted for embezzlement |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/01/113_80610.html |work=[[The Korea Times]] |date=30 January 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195134/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/01/113_80610.html |archivedate=29 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> and the Head of the Bugil Education Foundation as well as that of [[Bugil Academy]] and [[Bugil Girls' Academy]].

