{{Infobox Politician | name = Václav Fischer | image = | imagesize = | order = [[Senate of the Parliament of the Czech Republic|Senator]] from [[Prague 1]] | term_start = 28 August 1999 | term_end = 23 November 2002 | predecessor = | successor = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1954|06|22|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Prague]], [[Czechoslovakia]] | religion = | spouse = | profession = | party = }} '''Václav Fischer''' (born 22 June 1954) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]]-[[Germany|German]] [[businessman]] and [[politician]]. He was the founder of the companies [[CK Fischer]] and [[Fischer Air]].
He attended the [[University of Economics, Prague|University of Economics]] in [[Prague]]. After graduating from Internal Commerce Studies, Fischer moved to Switzerland for a short time, then he based in [[Berlin]] (then [[West Germany]]) and [[Hamburg]], where he worked for some travel agencies and a shipping company. In 1980 Fischer founded in Germany his own travel agency called [[Fischer Reisen]]. Due to his success, after the [[Velvet Revolution]] that ended the Czechoslovak communist dictatorship, Fischer decided to return to Czechoslovakia to establish the subsidiaries of his companies in the country, as well as to expand to other Central European countries, such as [[Hungary]], [[Slovakia]] and [[Poland]].<ref>{{cite news|title=A Slavic sun king|url=http://www.economist.com/node/666620|newspaper=The Economist|date=21 June 2001|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>
In 1995, he acquired some air routes of the airline [[Condor Flugdienst]] to create his own company, [[Fischer Air]].{{citation needed|date = May 2018}}
Fischer won a seat in the [[Senate of the Czech Republic]] in the [[Prague 1 by-election, 1999|1999 by-election for the Prague 1]] with 71.24% of the votes. Fischer was the first openly gay Czech parliamentarian.<ref>{{cite news|title=An Unusual Kind of Tolerance|url=https://www.respekt.cz/respekt-in-english/an-unusual-kind-of-tolerance|newspaper=Respekt Magazine|date=23 August 2013|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>
